description:
&lt;p&gt;Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust is currently seeking to appoint Staff Nurses to the Bank who will play an essential role in patient care. Frimley Health are a forward facing trust that is committed to excellence, and working together. The Temporary Staffing service is well established across all sites, including Heatherwood Hospital, Wexham Park Hospital and Frimley Park Hospital and numerous community sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working on the Bank, you have an opportunity to make a difference and work in a fast paced, highly rewarding environment. You will be eager to expand and develop your knowledge and experience, whilst having the flexibility to achieve a good work-life balance. Day to day you will be assisting patients, providing support to areas with high demand, and providing quality nursing. The versatility of the role enables you to work with a variety of patients, departments, and settings; making every day different.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both verbal and written communication skills, and experience of team working will be essential to the role. Strong interpersonal skills will also be essential. Relevant qualifications and NMC registration is necessary alongside at least 6 months acute experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through working for the trust you will have access to a range of training and staff benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
